The paper discusses the use of deep learning to capture the semantic structure and concepts of large structured documents, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) research. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning models, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper specifically mentions the use of deep learning, which is a subset of machine learning, and therefore cs.DL (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category.
